originalText.text:
Surprisingly pleased with this location, especially given the affordable price point. There are some floor organizational changes that need to be taken. It’s almost impossible to navigate the gym floor or get the equipment you want without interrupting someone or dangerously stepping through equipment that’s too close together. Also, remaining open until 11 PM would be FANTASTIC. There are days when i skip the gym just because the commute + the workout puts me past 10 PM.
The crew are friendly and would easily recommend this location to others.

originalText.text: Highly unprofessional gym with gate keeping mentality for potential customers. Came in for a 3-day trial. We’re transplants so we don’t have a local ID. Used a piece of mail to verify our residency. We were able to attend the first day of our trial. The following day attended, we were under a time constraint so we weren’t able to discuss membership plans with the sales team — but would be back the next day. We were given the door. Our original entitlement of a 3-day trial was revoked. This is very unprofessional for potential customers and quite mean. Not all residents of NYC are going to have a local ID. Other means were verified the first day and confirmed. The fact that it wasn’t protocol is not our fault.

originalText.text:
I’ve been going to this gym for about a decade. Checking in is an easy swipe. Several people who work there know my name and use it, which I appreciate. It’s clean, and my fellow co-members are courteous. I generally go early or mid afternoon; it’s not crowded at these times. They always have clean towels available. It’s a bit
more expensive than I would like, but in NYC, it could be worse. That’s the reason I’m doing 4 stars instead of 5, along with the policy of if you’re going to freeze your membership, it has to be on the first of the month.

originalText.text:
Sign up process was incredibly smooth, worked with John directly, he's incredibly customer focused, transparent, easy going and personable.  The gym itself has solid equipment,  great trainers and friendly people working the front desk.  Highly recommend,  and if you're looking for a new membership you can only go right asking for John

Quick update in 2.9.24
I unfortunately had to cancel my membership due to a change in circumstances and the team I worked with was so thorough and on top of it, worked through with me seamlessly.   Also there is new equipment that really opened up the cardio space.  This gym is great and even has improved since the time I was a member.

originalText.text: Yes, things are tight here, but it’s NYC, and if you can accept that then this gym will be of great service to you. The staff are pleasant, the equipment and facilities are clean, and everyone seems easy to workout around. It’s a solid gym at an affordable rate.
